snippet.title: PARIS TRAVEL GUIDE 2018 - What to do, top tips, and how to do it on a budget PARIS TRAVEL SERIES 4/4
snippet.description:
Planning a trip to Paris but don't know where to start or what to do? Our Paris Travel Guide 2018 - the fourth and final video in our Paris Travel Video series is here to help!

Sharing with you every top tip and recommendation we gained from our time in Paris, we'll be covering TRANSPORT - the best way to get to Paris and the best way to get around the city.

ACCOMMODATION - where to stay in Paris, Airbnb, hotel, or hostel?

PRICES - just how expensive is Paris? And how to do Paris on a budget!

and finally WHAT TO DO - the places you can't miss on a trip to Paris, like the Eiffel Tower, Montmartre, and some you may not have heard off.

Use our code for money off your first Airbnb stay ➜ https://www.airbnb.co.uk/c/nathanc3213

Let's Travel Together - Subscribe ➜ https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCWmBYPbsGaGDOo3UExFOCew?sub_confirmation=1

Check out our Paris Travel Series Playlist ➜ https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DB3ou65OQKQ&t=0s&list=PLqok0lDj33EarGfnMQKd8Ydohs9IsHMTv&index=3

Facebook - alwaysafriday
Instagram - alwaysafridaytravel
Travel Blog - alwaysafriday.com
Pinterest - alwaysafriday

If you liked the video we'd love it if you gave it a thumbs up!

Music from Epidemic Sound

replies.textDisplay: Paris is a city you can visit all year round, so there are always plenty of tourists. However, we found April to be a great sweetspot where the weather is pretty good (we were very lucky with 26C) and the crowds are minimal compared to peak times like August.

comments.textDisplay: If you go the first Sunday of each month a lot of the museums and art gall are free entry. A lot of restaurants in St Michel have €10-15 set menus. There is a fabulous restaurant la tavern de montmarte which is super cheap and so tasty. The eiffel tower is cheaper if you walk the steps to the first level and you can pre book tickets. The Parc at buttes chaumont is fabulous
